<TEXTAREA NAME="ReplyMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">[QUOTE]Originally posted by Erick:
[B]Mark of Karn - Strips any damage shield from a mob, anyone attacking the mob from that point on are healed 6 points every time they strike it with melee damage.

Mark of Retribution - This is a damage shield like thorns or immolation but with a twist.  You cast it on the mob and once it lands the mob takes 15 points of damage every time it lands a successful melee attack.  I haven't run into a damage shield yet that it doesn't stack with.

MoK is most useful when fighting mobs that make use of damage shields themselves.  A lot of the froggies in upper Sebilis for example.  Basically it can go in and strip out the damage shield without affecting any debuffs your group may have cast (slow, cripple etc).  The only other way to get rid of a mob's damage shield is to dispell them which would affect party debuffs as well.

I've found MoR most useful when in a small group or duoing.  It really is of limited usefullness if you have an enchanter or shaman in the group that is slowing the mobs.  But if its just you and a partner the fights are going to last long enough to get good damage from and unslowed mob.

MoK - Fairly rare drop from Sebelite Juggernauts in Sebilis and Guardian Wurms in Skyfire.

Mor - Fairly common drop in Fungus Grove, was never a merchant spell.  (Never believe everything you read on Castersrealm).


[/B][/QUOTE]

</TEXTAREA>
